  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Advantium — GE Monogram's tri-technology speed-cook oven</h2>
    <p>Advantium is GE's proprietary tri-technology speed-cook platform, introduced in the late 1990s and refined across multiple generations since. In the Monogram lineup, Advantium typically installs as the upper oven in a wall-oven column stack above a conventional lower Monogram wall oven — giving the kitchen both speed-cook capability (Advantium above) and conventional bake capability (Monogram wall oven below) in a unified column cutout.</p>
    <p><b>Three integrated heat technologies</b>:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><b>Halogen light</b> — halogen lamps above the cavity deliver intense radiant heat from above, cooking food surfaces quickly. Lamps are rated for defined operating hours and require periodic replacement.</li>
      <li><b>Convection</b> — circulated hot air evens cooking across the cavity. Convection element + fan motor architecture similar to conventional wall ovens but coordinated with other tech in Speedcook mode.</li>
      <li><b>Microwave</b> — standard microwave magnetron with the door-interlock safety architecture common to all microwaves. Three door-interlock switches typical; magnetron with power supply + diode + capacitor support circuitry.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><b>Service domains by technology</b>. Halogen service — lamp replacement $240-$420 per lamp-zone, typically scheduled rather than emergency. Microwave service — magnetron, interlocks, support circuitry $340-$620 depending on sub-fault. Convection service — element, fan motor, sensors $380-$640. Tri-tech control logic — firmware reset + update $220-$380; control board replacement $680-$1,080 when firmware work doesn't resolve.</p>
    <p><b>Advantium diagnostic approach</b>: establish which technology is involved in the presenting fault. Halogen lamp failure symptoms differ from microwave magnetron failure symptoms from convection element failure symptoms. Sometimes a fault spans multiple technologies (tri-tech control logic issue), and diagnostic isolates which sub-system is the root cause.</p>
  </div></section>

